    "author_channel_id": "UCBSqV7b6nnIFX0e0JuuzzTA",
    "text": "XY printers have been using drive belts for a long time, though I never would have guessed the reason.  Figures that XYZ printers would catch up.  What I want to know is when any printer manufacturers are going to start using the default drivers available in most operating systems, and when are we going to see printheads or belts that read their true position via a capacitive linear encoder.  Salutations!",
